The 48-year-old city worker was arrested in the German city of Hildesheim on Tuesday following an anonymous tip&nbsp;that he had been emptying parking machines and siphoning&nbsp;the money over more than two years.While the total damage is difficult to estimate, authorities said they calculated that the city's coffers had suffered a loss of around 21,000 euros in the first three months of this year alone.Police also disclosed that a sniffer dog had uncovered more than 15,000 euros in cash during a raid of suspect's apartment.The detained city worker reportedly confirmed the extent of his crimes as he was questioned by police.&nbsp;dm/kms (AP, dpa)